div.p:
For at the first, Maister Askam had much ado to make two or three verses in English: but now euery scholler can make some. What language so hard, harsh, or barbarous, that time and art will not amend? As I haue written in an other place, thus;




Naught can at once be begonne, or present made, to be perfect.

By trauel, all hard thinges are brought to singular effect.

Yet that Apelles could Cytheraeas beawty depolish;

Had not he time to delyne, hir picture finely to finnysh?
